<h2>But isn't it open-source software?</h2>
It has been open-source software since day one and still is today, as you can see in the <a href="https://mediaarea.net/en/MediaInfo/License">license</a>.<br/>
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source">Open-source</a> doesn't prohibit ads.<br/>

<h2>This is always displayed!</h2>
For the largest ads, there is an "X" on the top right of the ad in the MediaInfo interface that you can click to close it (it won't reappear quickly).<br/>

<h2>This is an anti-feature!</h2>
It depends on your point of view. Empty software or software with fewer features may be considered less good than software with an ad.

